cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper deals with the development of a large-scale dataset of annotated animal faces, which can be used for various computer vision tasks such as face alignment, detection, and recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for animal psychology understanding, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for automatic systems capable of interpreting animal faces, which can be considered as an application of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of the dataset for fine-grained recognition tasks, which can be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
